## Diagram Type Instructions

{% if diagram_type == "c4_container" %}
Generate a **C4 Container diagram** using Mermaid `graph TD` syntax.
- Show all major containers (web app, API, database, message broker, cache, etc.)
- Label each container with technology and responsibility
- Show all communication arrows with protocol labels (REST, gRPC, AMQP, SQL, etc.)
- Group containers into system boundary boxes where appropriate
- Include external systems/actors as distinct shapes
{% elif diagram_type == "sequence_primary" %}
Generate a **Sequence diagram** using Mermaid `sequenceDiagram` syntax.
- Show the **primary happy-path request flow** end-to-end
- Include all participants: client, gateway, services, databases, external systems
- Use `activate`/`deactivate` blocks to show processing scope
- Label every arrow with the operation, payload type, and HTTP method or protocol
- Show synchronous calls with solid arrows, async with dashed arrows
{% elif diagram_type == "sequence_error" %}
Generate an **Error Sequence diagram** using Mermaid `sequenceDiagram` syntax.
- Show the **primary failure/error scenario** (e.g. service unavailable, auth failure, timeout)
- Include retry logic, circuit breaker states, fallback paths
- Use `alt`/`else`/`opt` blocks for conditional branches
- Label all error responses with status codes and error types
{% elif diagram_type == "state" %}
Generate a **State diagram** using Mermaid `stateDiagram-v2` syntax.
- Show the lifecycle of the primary domain entity (order, job, request, etc.)
- Include all states: initial, intermediate, terminal (success and failure)
- Label transitions with triggering events and guards
- Use composite states (`state X { ... }`) for complex sub-states
{% elif diagram_type == "class" %}
Generate a **Class diagram** using Mermaid `classDiagram` syntax.
- Show the core domain model classes and their relationships
- Include fields with types and visibility modifiers
- Show inheritance, composition, aggregation, and dependency relationships
- Include key methods on service/repository classes
{% elif diagram_type == "er" %}
Generate an **Entity Relationship diagram** using Mermaid `erDiagram` syntax.
- Show all persisted entities and their attributes (type and key constraints)
- Use correct cardinality notation (||--o{, }|--|{, etc.)
- Label relationships with verb phrases
- Include primary keys, foreign keys, and important indexed fields
{% elif diagram_type == "deployment" %}
Generate a **Deployment diagram** using Mermaid `graph TD` syntax.
- Show physical infrastructure: cloud regions, availability zones, clusters, nodes
- Include: load balancers, container orchestration, databases, caches, CDNs
- Show traffic routing and replication topology
- Label services with replica counts, instance types, and scaling policies
{% elif diagram_type == "flowchart" %}
Generate a **Flowchart** using Mermaid `flowchart TD` syntax.
- Show the main data processing or business logic flow
- Include decision diamonds, process rectangles, and terminal ovals
- Show parallel paths with fork/join notation where applicable
- Label every edge with the condition or data that triggers it
{% endif %}

